import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.plot(data['date'], data['wounds'], label='Wounds', color='blue')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['other'], label='Other', color='green')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['disease'], label='Disease', color='red')

    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Cases')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wounds, other and disease cases over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['wounds'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Wounds cases')
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['wounds'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Wounds cases')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wounds cases?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    data.set_index('date', inplace=True)
    data[['wounds', 'other', 'disease']].plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    plt.title('What is the proportion of wounds cases compared to other and disease cases?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Cases')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Wounds', 'Other', 'Disease'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    data['total_cases'] = data['wounds'] + data['other'] + data['disease']
    daily_average = data['total_cases'].mean()
    
    ax = data.plot.bar(x='date', y='total_cases', legend=True, figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.axhline(y=daily_average, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {daily_average:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average number of cases per day?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
